Amen to James Van Bokkelen's comments. Security through obscurity (or unlisted
telephone numbers, for that matter) is no security at all.  It is utterly
trivial to write a program to probe interesting portions of the Internet
address space, even easier than it is to do a Wargames-style search of the
telephone network.  Unless your hosts implement proper security mechanisms
of their own, all you will do with your scheme is make life more difficult
for others.

Phil

